race.comment: SHARE THE JOY (10) is a twenty-seven-start maiden who has been in the money nine times. Ran on late when fourth over 1400m here at latest. Has recorded two top-three finishes from four runs at this venue. Well drawn and gets her chance. THE REEL PENELOPE (5) turned in a moderate effort on debut last start when eighth at Beaumont (Newcastle) over 1150m. Strips fitter and can play a leading role here. FLYING GREY (3) comes here on debut for the Brad Widdup stable with stable apprentice Poppie Gorton in the saddle. Her most recent trial at Kembla was sound and this is a very suitable race for her on debut. Can make an immediate impact. CASINO STING (6) looks suited by the rise in trip today and can improve.
